HEADWORD: Syriasm
<hw>Syr"i*asm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A Syrian idiom; a
Syrianism; a Syriacism.</def> <rj><au>M. Stuart.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Scripture Greek is observed to be full of <qex>Syriasms</qex>
and Hebraisms.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Warburton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

